    <h1 class="main">John Adams Service in the Continental Congress</h1>
    <h2 class="sub">Additional Committee Assignments<br/>29 August  12 October 1776</h2>
    <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> increasingly felt the weight of committee work during the six weeks that remained before he could take a much-needed rest. He un-<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-05-02-pb-0010">[10<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-05/ADMS-06-05-02-pb-0010.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>burdened himself about his need for relief in almost petulant tones to James Warren in more than one letter; yet for this period there is no significant documentary evidence of <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s contribution to committee reports. The editors are reduced simply to listing committee assignments and their consequences not previously mentioned. The form follows that of earlier lists in Volumes 3 and 4 which summarize <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s participation in committees.</p>
    <ul class="simple">
	  <li>
      <span title="marginal note in original"> Eliphalet Dyer, Thomas Lynch, John Jay, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, Francis Lewis, Thomas Heyward Jr., Lyman Hall, Benjamin Rush (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 2:250; 5:463, 636).</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">A standing committee to devise ways for supplying the Continental Army with medicines. See vol. <span>3:156</span>.</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">To consider a petition from Peter Dicthery (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 5:723).</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">Other duties assigned: 16 Sept.to consider a letter from Dr. William Rickman; 20 Sept.to forward 300 pounds of Peruvian Bark to the southern department; 23 Sept.to consider a letter from Dr. William Shippen; 24 Sept.to obtain medicines from the Pennsylvania Council of Safety (same, 5:761, 788, 809, 813).</span>
     </li>
	  <li>
      <span title="marginal note in original"> James Duane, George Wythe, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, Roger Sherman, Joseph Hewes, Thomas Johnson, William Whipple, Thomas Jefferson (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 4:293294; 5:608).</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">To ascertain the value of gold and silver coins in relation to Spanish milled dollars. See vol. <span>4:1718</span>.</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">Reported and report tabled: <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ draft ]">Dft</abbr> in the hand of Thomas Jefferson (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 5:724728; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Papers of Thomas Jefferson&lt;/i&gt;, ed. Julian P. Boyd and others, Princeton, 1950-. ]">Jefferson, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Papers</span></span>, 1:515518).</span>
     </li>
	  <li>
      <span title="marginal note in original"> Robert Morris, Richard Henry Lee, George Wythe, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 5:827).</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">To draft letters of credence for the commissioners to France and to suggest means for their subsistence.</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">Reported and resolutions adopted: 28 Sept.; <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ draft ]">Dft</abbr> not found (same, 5:833834).</span>
     </li>
	  <li>
      <span title="marginal note in original"> George Wythe, Francis Hopkinson, Edward Rutledge, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, Thomas Stone (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 5:830).</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">To consider two letters from George Washington of 24 and 25 Sept. with enclosures.</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">Reported and resolutions adopted: 30 Sept.; <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ draft ]">Dft</abbr> not found (same, 5:836837).</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">Further resolutions adopted: 7 Oct.; <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ draft ]">Dft</abbr> not found (same, 5:853).</span>
     </li>
	  <li>
      <span title="marginal note in original"> Richard Henry Lee, Roger Sherman, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, Elbridge Gerry (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 5:838).</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">To consult with Thomas Mifflin on his resumption of the post of quartermaster general.</span>
      <span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-05-02-pb-0011">[11<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-05/ADMS-06-05-02-pb-0011.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
      <span title="marginal note in original">Reported and resolutions adopted: 2 Oct.; <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ draft ]">Dft</abbr> not found (same, 5:839840).</span>
     </li>
	</ul>
